         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">7/7/94, ¶  ¶ Kindly remind me, dear Mr Potts about September, to send the root of the W. African Wonder-Grass, Panicum spectabile. It has in the cool weather gone back here, and it would do no good to...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">94.07.07</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Henry Potts</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>ML MSS.2697, Box K8313, Potts papers, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">proofed.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>7/7/94,</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Kindly remind me, dear Mr Potts about September, to send the root of the W. African Wonder-Grass, Panicum spectabile. It has in the cool weather gone back here, and it would do no good to plant it, while night frosts might occur In the first year after planting it should be lightly covered with bushes or hay, so as to allow the roots getting strength for perennial growth and spread.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If the enclosed Bamboo-seeds were sown in a warm house or forcing frame, the seedling could be gradually hardened off, and the plants when strong enough, would endure the winters there</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Your treatise on Sorghum is very interesting</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr Hartmann<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Probably the Qld botanical collector Carl Heinrich Hartmann, who died in December 1887.</p>
               </note> is dead since several years. Dr Bancroft sen. died last month,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Joseph Bancroft died on 16 June 1894.</p>
               </note> a great loss to Austral science.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You shall soon have some seeds of economic plants, they must be sown <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">after</hi>
               </seg> the night frosts have passed</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Do you like to join the Royal Hort. Soc of Engl. as FRHS? I will gladly propose you.</p>
         </div>
